args: The day is here at last! Today, we put\nOperation Help Emily Elope into action!
Yeah, eloping on the actual day of the\nwedding sounds suuuuper crazypants.\nAre we SURE sure this is a good idea?
It's the PERFECT day for it! All the players\nwill be at the venue at the same time,\nwhich means we'll trick everyone at once!
We all just need to play our parts,\nlike we discussed earlier.
The prince and Notte will stay with Emily.
I, of course, play the bamboozler bride,\nwhile Cleo and Elisanne are my escorts\nin case something goes amiss.
Come now, everyone! Off we go!\nLet's help Emily follow her heart\nand live her truest love!
Ladies and gentlemen, please fix your\nattention upon the lady of the hour!\nThe bride has arrived!
Who in the blazes are YOU?!\nAnd where is my daughter?!
But I met this woman earlier and she...\nWait. You are NOT Emily?!
Alas, I am not the daughter of a duke;\nI am the daughter of a pumpkin farmer!

Also, if I can make a quick sidebar here,
if you stew our pumpkins in a light broth,
they become delights without peer.
If anyone wants a recipe, I can—
Still your flapping gums, peasant!\nNone here care a whit for your gourds!
Servants! Stop gaping like the village idiot\nand seize this impostor at once!
Well, this could have gone better...\nCleo! Elisanne! To me!
Might I suggest a hasty retreat?\nWith the focus on the ＂hasty＂ part.
I must agree. This wedding is filled with\ncivilians, not soldiers. It would be a stain\nupon my honor to do battle with them.
Not to worry: I prepared a little spell\njust in case everything went haywire.\nAaaaand...ABRACADABRA!
What the...?! My clothes!\nThey're stuck to the table!
This is not a spell I've heard of before.
It's normally used by noblewomen to help\ntheir fancy strapless gowns stay in place.\nI just repurposed it a bit.
Magic is so very useful sometimes.
And the best part is that they can't\nchase after Emily either!
A thousand gold pieces for the man who\ncatches that fake and returns my daughter!
Xania, Emily's here. How'd the plan go?\nI bet they were all SO fooled!

Oh, uh, yep! They were fooled all right!
And this is TOTALLY unrelated, but we
miiight have a number of very angry
people chasing us at the moment.
Huh. I was so sure this would work...\nOkay, never mind. We'll hold them off;\nyou take Emily and get out of here!
Let's go, Emily! For your love!
*pant* *pant* Now that we've come\nthis far, they ought to be—
Oh no! It's one of the servants!\nWait, hold on. You're...
XANIA?! What are YOU doing here,\nsister-in-law?!
I should ask you the same question!
Well, before I married your brother,\nI was a maid at Lady Emily's manor.
I still fill in there from time to time when\nthings are slow on the pumpkin farm.
But my part in this isn't important.\nWhat are you even DOING, Xania?!
Well, you see, we had this great plan,\nbut then things sort of went...poorly.
I'm going to need you to sit down and\nexplain everything to me at some point.
But for now, Lady Emily, you must go back.\nI'm sure there's still time for the wedding\nto proceed this evening if we—
I love someone else, Mei, and we have\nsworn ourselves to each another.

I WILL marry my sweet babboo, even if it
means throwing away both my wealth
and standing. A life of poverty is a small
price to pay to be with the one I love!
But if I were to let you go, Lady Emily...
(She's right. If they find out Mei let\nEmily go, they'll fire her on the spot.)
Come, Xania. Let us be off.
...Er, Xania? Why are you...holding my\narm...and preventing me from leaving?!
(What do I DO?! I want Emily to be happy,\nbut not at the expense of Mei!)
...Keep her close while you run\nand don't look back!
If Lady Emily is truly in love, that is more\nprecious than any employment of mine.
Now get out of here already!
Th-thank you, Mei... Come on, Emily!\nWe have to go now!
We did it. We escaped.\nOh, thank you for everything!
I hope that one day you can be as happy as\nmy sweet babboo and I. Farewell, Xania!
(Look how happy she is. Emily is the\ntrue bride here, even if I am the one\nwearing the fancy dress.)
(Only a pure, unadulterated love could\npossibly make someone so happy.)
(If I could find that kind of passion,\nthen maybe I could...)
I hope you live happily ever after, Emily.
